channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Good News: Trump Just Nuked One Advantage Biden Did Have in Campaign
'I haven't decided': Mainstream Senate Dems hesitate on attending Netanyahu's address to Congress
item.description: Rank-and-file Democrats are hesitating to say whether they will attend the joint address to Congress by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu next month as the country continues to fight terrorist group Hamas in Gaza.

item.title: State Dept. Official, Critic of Israel Policy, Resigns
item.description: Andrew Miller, the deputy assistant secretary for Israel-Palestinian affairs is resigning, according to the Washington Post. Miller has been critical of the Biden administration's "bear hug" approach to Israel, but cited family as his reason for resigning.

item.title: Woke White 'Femicrats' Hold Hilarious Struggle Session After Report of Biden Losing Support Among Women
Biden's secret weapon in previous national debates may again be a factor during showdown with Trump
item.description: Amid concerns over President Biden's mental acuity fueled by social media videos and a troubling Wall Street Journal report, low debate expectations may play into his strategic advantage.

item.title: Reclusive Mellon Heir Donates $50M to Trump Super PAC
item.description: Reclusive billionaire Timothy Mellon, a day after former President Donald Trump was convicted of 34 felony counts in New York City, donated $50 million to the pro-Trump super PAC Make America Great Again Inc.

item.title: RNC Sues to Stop Vermont City's Non-Citizen Voting Rule
Trump mocks RFK Jr for not making debate stage: 'Maybe someday'
item.description: Former President Trump released a video on Thursday saying he would "love to have" Robert F. Kennedy Jr. on the debate stage but mocked the independent candidate for failing to qualify.

item.title: Trump Attorneys Contest Jack Smith's Appointment
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's legal team is arguing special counsel Jack Smithâ€™s appointment was unconstitutional.

item.title: CNN's Own Legal Analyst Lays Waste to Panel for Saying Supreme Court Is Delaying Trump Immunity Decision
White House finalizes rules increasing clean energy subsidies fivefold in bid to support green jobs
item.description: The White House finalized new rules under the Inflation Reduction Act aimed at forwarding President Biden's vision of better-paying green energy jobs.

item.title: Biden Attorney Preparing for 2024 Voter Fraud Claims
item.description: President Joe Biden's personal attorney indicated he's preparing for possible legal challenges after November's general election, Politico reported.

item.title: Lock Him Up! Voters Want Merrick Garland Removed From Office, Tossed in Prison for Protecting Biden
Supreme Court upholds federal gun ban for those under domestic violence restraining orders
item.description: Friday's decision in U.S. v. Rahimi, could have major implications for several pending gun-rights cases and legislative measures.

item.title: More Weighty Issues Await Supreme Court
item.description: The Supreme Court is headed into its final week with about a quarter of the cases heard this year still undecided, including ones that could reshape the law on abortion, social media, and other issues.
